        <h1>Travel to Durango</h1>
    
        <h2>What is durango?</h2>
    
        <p>Durango is the capital city of the state of Durango, Mexico. It is known for its historic center, with important Mexican Baroque and colonial buildings. Construction began in 1695 on the ornate Cathedral Basilica, which has sacred art and wood carvings in its interior. The Museo de la Ciudad 450, in a converted palace, has exhibits tracing the city's history. Bebeleche is a modern museum with interactive exhibits on science and culture.</p>
        
        <h3>Things to do: </h3>
    
     <ul>
        <li>Visit the Cathedral Basilica of Durango</li>
        <li>Walk through the Plaza de Armasr</li>
        <li>Practice extreme sports</li>
        <li>Visit the Paseo del Viejo Oeste</li>
    </ul>
    
    <img src="https://www.kasandbox.org/programming-images/creatures/Hopper-Jumping.png" alt="A jumping Beaver" >
    
