    <h2>Interesting facts</h2>
    
        <p>The name Durango comes from Basque and means "place of water", it was founded 456 years ago. Its official name of the city of Durango is Victoria de Durango, in honor of Guadalupe Victoria, the first president of Mexico; the Durango National Fair is the most important in northern Mexico and the second most important in Mexico in the Fair-exhibition category. The Historic Center of the capital of Durango is the place where most of the architectural and cultural heritage of the city is found.</p>
